Pluralization affects user experience by ensuring correct grammar in dynamic content. For example, distinguishing between '2 items' and '2 boxes' requires logic like:
javascript
function pluralize(count, singular, plural) {
  return count === 1 ? singular : plural;
}
console.log(`${count} ${pluralize(count, 'item', 'items')}`);

Attention to such details enhances clarity and professionalism in UI text.
